    "Conventional transgressions, by contrast, usually do not cause direct harm to a person and are perceived as wrong only by mere social convention.",
    "The transgressions in the scenarios for which moral evaluations were provided in this study are noted in Table 3 (see Supplementary Information for full details).",
    "Each passage consisted of a textual response to the question of why a given transgression is or is not morally wrong.",
    "One passage in each pair was authored by a human being (obtained from pretesting in a university sample), and the other was authored by a computer, namely, OpenAI's generative language model, GPT-4 (see Supplementary Information for more information about stimulus development.)",
    "We used GPT-4 45 because it is regarded as the most powerful engine behind the widely used tool, ChatGPT 46, 47."
